{% extends './_layouts/base.njk' %}

{% from './components/button/button.njk' import button %}

{% block title %}
  frōntensō-11ty-starter
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <canvas class="fixed top-0 left-0 w-full h-full" data-canvas></canvas>
  <video preload
    loop
    autoplay
    muted
    playsinline
    class="hidden fixed"
    data-video>
    <source src="/running-man.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  </video>
  <div id="smooth-wrapper">
    <div id="smooth-content">
      <div class="container" data-container>
        <div class="heading-container h-[100vh] flex justify-center items-center"
          data-snap>
          <h1 data-heading
            class="relative -top-8 text-center text-white text-8xl pointer-events-none opacity-0"
            aria-hidden="true"
            data-lag="0.5">
            Just Keep Running
          </h1>
        </div>
        <div class="text-gray-400 text-[6vw] md:text-[3vw] lg:text-[2vw] relative md:max-w-[80vw] lg:max-w-[50vw] leading-[1.5] ml-auto mr-auto text-center">
          <div class="h-screen flex items-center justify-center" data-snap>
            <p data-paragraph data-lag="0.5">
              &laquo;When I&rsquo;m criticized unjustly (from my&nbsp;viewpoint,
              at&nbsp;least), or&nbsp;when someone I&rsquo;m sure will
              understand me&nbsp;doesn&rsquo;t, I&nbsp;go running for
              a&nbsp;little longer than usual.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="h-screen flex items-center justify-center" data-snap>
            <p data-paragraph data-lag="0.5">
              By&nbsp;running longer it&rsquo;s like&nbsp;I can physically
              exhaust that portion of&nbsp;my&nbsp;discontent. It&nbsp;also
              makes me&nbsp;realize again how weak I&nbsp;am, how limited
              my&nbsp;abilities are. I&nbsp;become aware, physically,
              of&nbsp;these low points.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="h-screen flex items-center justify-center" data-snap>
            <p data-paragraph data-lag="0.5">
              And one of&nbsp;the results of&nbsp;running a&nbsp;little farther
              than usual is&nbsp;that&nbsp;I&nbsp;become that much stronger.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="h-screen flex items-center justify-center" data-snap>
            <p data-paragraph data-lag="0.5">
              That&rsquo;s the way I&rsquo;ve always lived. I&nbsp;quietly
              absorb the things I&rsquo;m able&nbsp;to, releasing them later,
              and in&nbsp;as&nbsp;changed a&nbsp;form as&nbsp;possible,
              as&nbsp;part of&nbsp;the story line in&nbsp;a&nbsp;novel.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="h-screen flex items-center justify-center" data-snap>
            <p data-paragraph data-lag="0.5">
              If&nbsp;I&rsquo;m angry, I&nbsp;direct that anger toward myself.
              If&nbsp;I&nbsp;have a&nbsp;frustrating experience, I&nbsp;use that
              to&nbsp;improve myself.&raquo;
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="h-screen flex items-center justify-center" data-snap>
            <p data-paragraph data-lag="0.5">
              Excerpt From <br />
              <span class="text-white">
                What I&nbsp;Talk About When I&nbsp;Talk About Running
              </span><br />
              by <span class="text-white">Haruki Murakami</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
